    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Check Side Clearance of Oil Control Ring Groove
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Check Side Clearance of Oil Control Ring Groove</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the outer edge of a new piston ring in the oil control ring groove. Roll the piston
                ring in its respective groove entirely around the piston. Make sure the ring is free in the groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200729" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Side Clearance of the Oil Control Ring Groove</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Ring Groove</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to check the side clearance of each oil control ring in its respective
                groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Tight side clearance may indicate carbon build up in the ring groove. The ring groove must be
                    cleaned.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Excessive side clearance indicates ring groove wear. The piston must be replaced.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
